I am very disappointed in the unprofessionalism this establishment has. Their lack of regard for humanity is disgusting. My father who is 71 years old and suffers from Parkinson’s disease and is an insulin dependent Diabetic  came to this particular restaurant. He explained to one of the managers that he was not feeling well. He asked if he could sit down to gather himself in order to call my brother. He was denied a seat. Both “managers were rude to him”.  He had asked the “managers” why were they treating him like the guys from Starbucks? After hearing this I was upset.  I called the establishment and asked for the manager. I asked the gentleman what was the policy regarding allowing individuals to  come into their establishment to have a seat. The man hung up the phone. I called back. I asked to speak with the Manager again, this time he was reluctant to tell me. He then Asked for my name and I told him. He said that his name was Bryan (and I’m not really sure if it was). I asked him did he hang up on me? He denied it. I asked “Bryan” again what was the policy regarding people not patronizing their business and requesting a seat. I was told that they ask those individuals to leave. I spoke to him and I asked him did he remember my father who came in. My father is 6’8, i’m Sure not too many elderly tall men could be forgotten about. I had explained to him that my father stated to the other gentleman that he wasn’t feeling well. I asked him not to treat anyone else like that because you never know what people are going through. He did apologize. However, I am not sure if my words truly carried. As a human being, he should’ve had way more respect for my father than that. I cannot image telling someone who is elderly stating they had Parkinson’s and being able to visibly it, saying NO. I will never again support a business like Jimmy Johns. What I will do is support the Brown Hotel across the street. My father was able to make it across the street to that hotel and asked one of the Bell serviceman for help. He explained that he needed help calling my brother because his hands were shaking really bad and he didn’t feel well. So you know what the gentleman did? He treated my father like a HUMAN BEING!!!! He offered my father a glass of water and ginger ale. He helped my father call my brother for help. My father cried while telling me this. He thanks God that someone saw him and helped him. He felt hurt and humiliated by the people at Jimmy Johns. To the man that helped my father thank you soooooo much. To Jimmy Johns. I’m still debating on calling the news about how you discriminated against my father. All he needed was help. Chasing a dollar should not mean more than helping your fellow man. Shame on you.

We order from this location a lot and normally have fast accurate service. However because of how they handled the one time we did have a problem is the reason for this low rating. We ordered 2 sandwiches and only one was delivered. I called the store and told that I was wrong and two were delivered. After speaking to the manager I was told the missing sandwich would be made and sent out right away. After 30mins, we still had not received the missing sandwich. I called a 2nd time and was told it was on the way. We finally received the missing sandwich 45mins after the first one was delivered. And we were offered nothing in way of an apology or gift card for their mistake. My fiance was on his lunch break and ended up not being able to eat because from the time I originally placed the order to when he got his missing sandwich it was over an hour later.
